<title>BELGIUM: EU investigating aid to Arbed steel group.</title>
<headline>EU investigating aid to Arbed steel group.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The European Commission said on Friday it had opened an investigation into aid granted by Luxembourg to steel group Arbed SA for research and development projects in 1995 and 1996.</p>
<p>The Commission said in a statement it was having trouble determining whether the aid, 65 million Luxembourg francs ($1.8 million), was compatible with EU state aid rules.</p>
<p>It said the rules state that governments may provide aid only as an &quot;incentive&quot; for research projects. However, in Arbed's case, the money was granted after the projects had been completed, it said.</p>
<p>&quot;The Commission notes that the Luxembourg authorities have not proved...that the companies in quesion are conducting or have conducted more research than they would have without aid,&quot; it said.</p>
</text>
